    <div class="tile is-parent is-8">
      <article class="tile is-child box">
        <p class="title">How to build a profesisonal Resume:</p>
        <p class="subtitle">What should your resume include?</p>
        <div class="content">
          <p> Your resume is the first thing employers will see when they think about hiring you for a position or not. But a resume is more than just a list of your accreditations, skills, and work history. Your resume should show a potential employer that you would be a crucial asset to the team and not bringing you aboard would be a mistake. 
          </p>
          <p>
               Your resume should include your motivations, goals, and even some reasons you are interested in the field. It is important to not overload your resume with content that downs out your acconplishments. If your employer was only going to skim thorugh your resume once what would you want them to know about yourself? The first impression your resume gives may be the deciding factor in whther you get an interview or not so put care into your creation. 
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
